{"title_page": "Will Wood", "text_new": "{{Similar names|Willie Wood (disambiguation)|William Wood (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = Will Wood\n|image       = \n|image_size  = \n|caption     = \n|fullname    = William Nicholas Wood<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/698753|title=Premier League clubs publish released lists|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=11 June 2018|publisher=Premier League}}</ref>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1996|11|29|df=y}}<ref name=\"11v11\"/>\n|birth_place = [[Burgess Hill]], England \n|height      = 1.74m<ref name=\"11v11\">{{cite web |title=Will Wood|url=https://www.11v11.com/players/will-wood-254019/|publisher=11v11 |accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n|position    = [[Defender (association football)|Left back]]\n|currentclub = [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]]\n|clubnumber  = 17\n|youthyears1 = 2008\u20132018\n|youthclubs1 = [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n|years1      = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs1      = [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]]\n|caps1       = 4\n|goals1      = 0\n|years2      = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs2      = \u2192 [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]] (loan)\n|caps2       = 8\n|goals2      = 0\n|years3      = 2019\u2013\n|clubs3      = [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]]\n|caps3       = 4\n|goals3      = 0\n|club-update = 16:29, 25 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''William Nicholas Wood''' (born 29 November 1996) - not to be confused with the American singer-songwriter of the same name - is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]], as a [[Defender (association football)|left back]].\n\n==Early and personal life==\nWood grew up in [[Burgess Hill]] and attended [[Oakmeeds Community College]].<ref name = \"MST\"/>\n\n==Career==\nWood joined [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] at the age of 11, signing a three-year professional contract in April 2015.<ref name = \"MST\">{{cite web|url=https://www.midsussextimes.co.uk/sport/football/dream-comes-true-for-will-wood-as-he-signs-professional-contract-at-southampton-1-6703638|title=Dream comes true for Will Wood as he signs professional contract at Southampton|date=22 April 2015|accessdate=31 May 2018|author=Mark Durnford|publisher=Mid Sussex Times}}</ref> He trialled with [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] in December 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/pompey/all-you-need-to-know-about-pompey-triallist-wood-1-8308457|title=All you need to know about Pompey triallist Wood|date=28 December 2017|accessdate=31 May 2018|author=Will Rooney|publisher=Portsmouth News}}</ref> and signed a one-year contract with [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] in May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44319068|title=Will Wood: Accrington Stanley sign Southampton defender|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=31 May 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 14 August 2018, in the [[EFL Cup]].<ref name = \"2018-19\"/> In October 2018 he moved on loan to [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.havantandwaterloovillefc.co.uk/articles/2018/10/13/will-wood-signs-for-the-hawks.html|title=WILL WOOD SIGNS FOR THE HAWKS|date=13 October 2018|accessdate=26 October 2018|publisher=Havant & Waterlooville F.C.}}</ref>\n\nHe was released by Accrington at the end of the 2018\u201319 season.{{cite web|url=https://accringtonstanley.co.uk/2019/05/stanley-retained-list/|title=Stanley\u2019s retained list|date=7 May 2019|accessdate=7 May 2019|publisher=Accrington Stanley F.C.}}</ref>\n\nHe signed for [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] in June 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barkinganddagenhampost.co.uk/sport/football/dagenham-and-redbridge/daggers-sign-youngster-wood-1-6130230|title=Daggers sign youngster Wood from Accrington Stanley|first=Jacob|last=Ranson|website=Barking and Dagenham Post}}</ref> and stated that he was looking forward to playing for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barkinganddagenhampost.co.uk/sport/football/dagenham-and-redbridge/daggers-signing-wood-up-for-the-challenge-1-6135040|title=Daggers Wood looking forward to the challenge of the National League|first=Jacob|last=Ranson|website=Barking and Dagenham Post}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 23 November 2019}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=2|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Southampton F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Southampton U23]]\n|2017\u201318<ref name = \"2017-18\">{{soccerbase season|96381|2017|accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n|colspan=3|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||3{{efn|name=EFT}}||0||3||0\n|-\n|[[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Accrington Stanley F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name = \"2018-19\">{{soccerbase season|96381|2018|accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League One|League One]]\n|4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||1||0||1{{efn|name=EFT|Appearance(s) in [[EFL Trophy]]}}||0||6||0\n|-\n|[[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]] (loan)\n|[[2018\u201319 National League|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"SW\">{{soccerway|william-wood/454237|accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n|[[National League (division)|National League]]\n|8||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||9||0\n|-\n|[[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] \n|[[2019\u201320 National League|2019\u201320]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|National League\n|4||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0||4||0\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!16!!0!!1!!0!!1!!0!!4!!0!!22!!0\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Dagenham & Redbridge F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wood, Will}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Southampton F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Accrington Stanley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Havant & Waterlooville F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Dagenham & Redbridge F.C. players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Similar names|Willie Wood (disambiguation)|William Wood (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = Will Wood\n|image       = \n|image_size  = \n|caption     = \n|fullname    = William Nicholas Wood<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/698753|title=Premier League clubs publish released lists|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=11 June 2018|publisher=Premier League}}</ref>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1996|11|29|df=y}}<ref name=\"11v11\"/>\n|birth_place = [[Burgess Hill]], England \n|height      = 1.74m<ref name=\"11v11\">{{cite web |title=Will Wood|url=https://www.11v11.com/players/will-wood-254019/|publisher=11v11 |accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n|position    = [[Defender (association football)|Left back]]\n|currentclub = [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]]\n|clubnumber  = 17\n|youthyears1 = 2008\u20132018\n|youthclubs1 = [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n|years1      = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs1      = [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]]\n|caps1       = 4\n|goals1      = 0\n|years2      = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs2      = \u2192 [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]] (loan)\n|caps2       = 8\n|goals2      = 0\n|years3      = 2019\u2013\n|clubs3      = [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]]\n|caps3       = 4\n|goals3      = 0\n|club-update = 16:29, 25 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''William Nicholas Wood''' (born 29 November 1996) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]], as a [[Defender (association football)|left back]].\n\n==Early and personal life==\nWood grew up in [[Burgess Hill]] and attended [[Oakmeeds Community College]].<ref name = \"MST\"/>\n\n==Career==\nWood joined [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] at the age of 11, signing a three-year professional contract in April 2015.<ref name = \"MST\">{{cite web|url=https://www.midsussextimes.co.uk/sport/football/dream-comes-true-for-will-wood-as-he-signs-professional-contract-at-southampton-1-6703638|title=Dream comes true for Will Wood as he signs professional contract at Southampton|date=22 April 2015|accessdate=31 May 2018|author=Mark Durnford|publisher=Mid Sussex Times}}</ref> He trialled with [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] in December 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/pompey/all-you-need-to-know-about-pompey-triallist-wood-1-8308457|title=All you need to know about Pompey triallist Wood|date=28 December 2017|accessdate=31 May 2018|author=Will Rooney|publisher=Portsmouth News}}</ref> and signed a one-year contract with [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] in May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44319068|title=Will Wood: Accrington Stanley sign Southampton defender|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=31 May 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 14 August 2018, in the [[EFL Cup]].<ref name = \"2018-19\"/> In October 2018 he moved on loan to [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.havantandwaterloovillefc.co.uk/articles/2018/10/13/will-wood-signs-for-the-hawks.html|title=WILL WOOD SIGNS FOR THE HAWKS|date=13 October 2018|accessdate=26 October 2018|publisher=Havant & Waterlooville F.C.}}</ref>\n\nHe was released by Accrington at the end of the 2018\u201319 season.{{cite web|url=https://accringtonstanley.co.uk/2019/05/stanley-retained-list/|title=Stanley\u2019s retained list|date=7 May 2019|accessdate=7 May 2019|publisher=Accrington Stanley F.C.}}</ref>\n\nHe signed for [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] in June 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barkinganddagenhampost.co.uk/sport/football/dagenham-and-redbridge/daggers-sign-youngster-wood-1-6130230|title=Daggers sign youngster Wood from Accrington Stanley|first=Jacob|last=Ranson|website=Barking and Dagenham Post}}</ref> and stated that he was looking forward to playing for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barkinganddagenhampost.co.uk/sport/football/dagenham-and-redbridge/daggers-signing-wood-up-for-the-challenge-1-6135040|title=Daggers Wood looking forward to the challenge of the National League|first=Jacob|last=Ranson|website=Barking and Dagenham Post}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 23 November 2019}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=2|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Southampton F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Southampton U23]]\n|2017\u201318<ref name = \"2017-18\">{{soccerbase season|96381|2017|accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n|colspan=3|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||3{{efn|name=EFT}}||0||3||0\n|-\n|[[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Accrington Stanley F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name = \"2018-19\">{{soccerbase season|96381|2018|accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League One|League One]]\n|4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||1||0||1{{efn|name=EFT|Appearance(s) in [[EFL Trophy]]}}||0||6||0\n|-\n|[[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]] (loan)\n|[[2018\u201319 National League|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"SW\">{{soccerway|william-wood/454237|accessdate=5 